The paper deals with the problem of signal recovery from linear observations, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), computer vision (cs.CV), and statistical learning (cs.SI). The use of quantization and dithering techniques is also relevant to these subfields. Therefore, these five categories are likely to be relevant to this paper, with cs.IT and cs.LG being the most likely ones.
